Add comprehensive test suite for VishwamAI kernels
- Introduced a structured test suite in the `tests` directory for VishwamAI kernels across TPU, GPU, and CPU platforms. - Created a README.md file detailing setup instructions, test organization, and performance benchmarks. - Implemented pytest configuration in `conftest.py` to manage platform-specific test requirements and device availability checks. - Developed a test runner script (`run_tests.py`) to facilitate running tests with various configurations. - Added unit and integration tests in `test_kernels.py` covering matrix operations, attention mechanisms, layer operations, and optimizers. - Established a requirements file (`requirements-test.txt`) for managing test dependencies across platforms. - Implemented expert balancing utilities in `moe_balance.py` to optimize expert placement across devices.
